                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="jms-0037.xml" title="Wild category" addr="jms-0037" type="local">wild categories</fr:link>. A <fr:em>wild 0-functor</fr:em> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is given by the following data:</fr:p>
                <fr:ol><fr:li>a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {ob}_{F} : \mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}\to \mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A,B:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex>, a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {hom}_{F} : \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {D}}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbf {ob}_{F}A,\mathbf {ob}_{F}B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
