                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="jms-0037.xml" title="Wild category" addr="jms-0037" type="local">wild categories</fr:link>. A <fr:em>wild 1-semi-functor</fr:em> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is given by a wild 0-functor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F : \mathcal {C}\to \mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> equipped with, for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f:\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (C,D\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g : \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (C,D\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, an identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {seq}_F\,f\,g : \mathbf {hom}_{F}{\mathopen {}\left (f;g\right )\mathclose {}} = \mathbf {hom}_{F}{f};\mathbf {hom}_{G}{g} ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
