                <fr:addr type="user">jms-003C</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-003C.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="The wild identity functor">The wild identity functor</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-0037.xml" title="Wild category" addr="jms-0037" type="local">wild category</fr:link>; the <fr:em>identity 0-functor</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {{1_{\mathcal {C}}}}{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> is defined as follows:</fr:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {aligned}
  \mathbf {ob}_{1_{\mathcal {C}}}A   & :\equiv  A \\
  \mathbf {hom}_{1_{\mathcal {C}}}f & :\equiv  f
\end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
                <fr:p>The above may be extended to a <fr:link href="jms-003F.xml" title="Wild 1-semi-functor" addr="jms-003F" type="local">wild 1-semi-functor</fr:link> as follows:</fr:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[  \mathsf {seq}_{F}\,f\,g :\equiv  \mathsf {refl}
]]></fr:tex>
              </fr:mainmatter>
