                <fr:title text="The wild constant functor">The wild constant functor</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="jms-0037.xml" title="Wild category" addr="jms-0037" type="local">wild categories</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> be an object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>. We define the <fr:em>constant 0-functor</fr:em> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> out of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> to be the <fr:link href="jms-0038.xml" title="Wild 0-functor" addr="jms-0038" type="local">0-functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {{\Delta  D}}{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> defined as follows:</fr:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {aligned}
  \mathbf {ob}_{\Delta  D}C    & :\equiv  D       \\
  \mathbf {hom}_{\Delta  D} f & :\equiv  1_{D}
\end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
                <fr:p>The above may be extended to a <fr:link href="jms-003F.xml" title="Wild 1-semi-functor" addr="jms-003F" type="local">wild 1-semi-functor</fr:link> as follows:</fr:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathsf {seq}_{F}\,f\,g :\equiv  \mathsf {refl}
]]></fr:tex>
              </fr:mainmatter>
